item.dc:creator: @pimjong pimjong
item.description:
@pimjong wrote:

[quote=“quaker2390, post:8, topic:2938”]deobfuscate…all right guys, it’s all really funny, we all know you made that word up…but, seriously, some of us are stupid…for future reference, I will post the definition-deobfuscate: no entry found for deobfusctae…obfuscate: 1.To make so confused or opaque as to be difficult to perceive or understand: â€œA great effort was made… to obscure or obfuscate the truthâ€ (Robert Conquest).
2.To render indistinct or dim; darken: The fog obfuscated the shore.
I still don’t get it though…someone put it in stupid, please…[/quote]
Like you wrote, obfuscating means making difficult to understand. That is exactly what obfuscating does. It changes the java/class file to make it unreadable. Deobfuscating is the opposite. That is why we are sometimes talking about DEOBS (deobfuscated clients/deobed clients etc).
Now, i only have 1 thing to say… Eat my poo.
